The LeastOccupiedComparator class is a comparator for sorting docking stations based on their occupancy level.

The LeastOccupiedStation class implements the SortingPolicy interface and defines a sorting policy based on the occupancy level of docking stations.
Main
This class represents the main entry point of the MyVelib application.

The MechanicalBicycle class represents a mechanical bicycle.

The MostUsedComparator class implements the Comparator interface to compare docking stations based on their usage.

The MostUsedStation class implements the SortingPolicy interface to sort docking stations based on their usage.
MyVelib
The MyVelib class represents a Velib network and manages its users and docking stations.
MyVelibNetwork
The MyVelibNetwork class represents the main entry point for the MyVelib network program.
Normal
The Normal class represents a default sorting policy for determining the optimal itinerary of a user's trip.
ParkingSlot
The ParkingSlot class represents a parking slot for bicycles.
Planner
Represents a planner for finding an optimal itinerary.
PlannerTest
 
PlanningPolicy
The PlanningPolicy interface defines the contract for a planning policy used to determine the optimal itinerary for a given start location, end location, and bicycle type.
PreferPlus
The PreferPlus class represents a sorting policy that prefers docking stations with plus type when determining the optimal itinerary for a user's trip.
PreferStreetBike
The PreferStreetBike class represents a sorting policy that prefers street bikes over other bikes when determining the optimal itinerary for a user's trip.
SortingPolicy
The SortingPolicy interface defines the contract for a sorting policy used to sort docking stations.
StationBalance
The StationBalance class represents the balance of a docking station, including the total number of rents and returns.
Terminal
The Terminal class represents a terminal in the myVelib system.
UniformDistributionBikes
The UniformDistributionBikes class represents a sorting policy that aims to distribute the bikes uniformly when determining the optimal itinerary for a user's trip.
User
The User class represents a user in the myVelib system.
UserBalance
The UserBalance class represents the balance of a user, including the number of rides, total rent time, total charges, and time-credit earned.
